<section class="hero">
  <h1>Eleven for families</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Eleven exists because a kid wanted to message their friends and every app
    said no: wrong device, no phone number, too young, or sign here for ads.
    Eleven says yes.
  </p>
  <div class="cta">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/#get">Get Eleven</a>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://home.elevenmessenger.com">Create your space</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-group" aria-label="Why families pick Eleven">
  <ul class="cards">
    <li>
      <h3>Safe for kids</h3>
      <p>
        A grown-up runs the space and decides who’s in it. No strangers, no
        feed, no follower counts, nothing built to keep anyone scrolling.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>No phone number needed</h3>
      <p>
        Kids without SIMs, tablets, hand-me-down iPads. Everyone joins with
        a link from you.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Every device welcome</h3>
      <p>
        iPhone in one pocket, Android in another, a school Chromebook at
        home. Any browser runs the full app; Mac and iPhone get native ones.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Family photos stay in the family</h3>
      <p>
        Photos are encrypted on your device before they leave it, and
        location data is stripped automatically. We can’t see them. Nobody
        can.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>The family logistics</h3>
      <p>
        Shared to-do lists. Reminders that nudge the whole chat — bins out,
        practice at six. Ask Eleven, the built-in helper, and it sets them
        up.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Grandparent-friendly</h3>
      <p>
        Nothing to install unless they want to, text as big as they need,
        and read messages stay read on every device.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem">
    <a href="/features/">All the features &rarr;</a>
  </p>
</section>

<section class="feature-group" aria-label="Pricing for families">
  <h2>What it costs</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">
    Joining is always free. Only the person who runs the space pays, and
    only if they want more room.
  </p>
  <div class="plans">
    <div class="plan">
      <h3>Free</h3>
      <span class="price">&euro;0</span>
      <p>
        Every feature. Up to three spaces, 1&nbsp;GB of photos and files
        each.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="plan featured">
      <h3>Family</h3>
      <span class="price">&euro;5<small>/year</small></span>
      <p>
        5&nbsp;GB of storage and your space is never tidied away as unused.
        One coffee, once a year.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="fine" style="margin-top: 1.25rem">
    Every plan has every feature — privacy is never the paid tier. Upgrade
    from <a href="https://home.elevenmessenger.com">your home page</a>;
    payment happens on Stripe’s page, so we never see your card. We do get
    the billing email — paying is the one time we need to know who you are.
  </p>
</section>

